(nICacheWays, power_leakage).explanation: Increasing the number of instruction cache ways requires more transistors and memory cells, which directly increases static power consumption due to leakage currents in the additional hardware components;

(nICacheWays, area_cell_area).explanation: More instruction cache ways require additional memory arrays and associated circuitry, directly increasing the total cell area needed for the cache implementation;

(nICacheWays, nDCacheMSHRs).explanation: The number of instruction cache ways and data cache miss status holding registers are independent architectural parameters that serve different functions in the memory hierarchy;
